 Tirith.","aliases":["Lady of the Golden Wood","Lady of Lórien","Elbereth"]},{"name":"Celeborn","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of the King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Lord of Lothlórien, husband to Galadriel.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Arrives in Minas Tirith.","aliases":[]},{"name":"Barahir","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Gondor","description":"Grandson of the Steward Faramir, author of the abbreviated version of The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Wrote The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen for the history of Gondor."},{"name":"Findegil","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King's Writer who completed the Thain's Book.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Completed a copy of the Red Book in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Sackville-Baggins family, rival of the Baggins family, known for her jealousy and desire to inherit Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"Husband"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Rival"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Antagonist"}],"recentEvents":"Visited Frodo and pestered him about Bilbo's will, accusing him of being a Brandybuck."},{"name":"Gildor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elf who encountered Frodo and his companions, giving them guidance and warning of peril.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met and gave advice to"}],"recentEvents":"Met Frodo and gave him warnings about enemies and advised him to take friends with him."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire known for his dogs and mushrooms.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Provided hospitality and transportation to the Ring-bearers."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty Bolger"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: Three is Company","currentLocation":"Crickhollow","description":"A hobbit from the Eastfarthing with an aversion to travel who was tasked with staying behind to deceive potential trackers.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to stay behind to pretend Frodo was still at Crickhollow."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil","aliases":["None","Master of the Green Path","Iarwain Ben-Adar","Master of Lake and Wood","Master of Many Songs"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mysterious man of the forest who lives in the lands near the Shire. He possesses the power to repel the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guided by him"}],"recentEvents":"Guided and protected the hobbits from the Black Riders, leading them back to the Road and to the village of Bree."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Queen of the River"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"House near the village of Stock","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she is known as the Queen of the River and is believed to have some magical or mystical powers associated with water.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippen","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed the hobbits, served them a supper and sang songs."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butler","Barley","Barliman","Mr. Butterbur"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Bree","description":"Keeper of The Prancing Pony inn in Bree, known for his good intentions and poor memory.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Accommodated him and other travelers"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Has a significant relationship for information exchange and hospitality"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo and his friends about troubles in the Shire and celebrated their return after a year of fears and uncertainties."},{"name":"Aragorn","aliases":["Thorongil","Dúnadan","Strider","Elessar","Dunedain Ranger","Estel","Aragorn, son of Arathorn","Arnor","Estë","Longshanks","Elfstone"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of the King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Heir to the throne of Gondor and descendant of Elendil. Known as the 'Evenstar' of Men and Elves. Leader of the resistance against Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Father-in-law"},{"character":"Arwen","relationship":"Future wife"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Mentor and advisor"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Friend and companion"}],"recentEvents":"Weds Arwen Undómiel in the City of Minas Tirith. Grows a sapling of the White Tree and plants it in the Citadel."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","last_seen":"Strider","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"A local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo's vanishing act.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Asserted he saw Frodo vanish into thin air, causing an uproar."},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"An inn servant who helps Frodo and his companions.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant and confidant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"servant and confidant"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"servant and confidant"}],"recentEvents":"Nob assists in the preparation and safety arrangements of the hobbits' rooms at the Prancing Pony Inn."},{"name":"Glorfindel","aliases":["Elrond's emissary","The Bright Elf"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of the King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Elven lord from Rivendell, famous for defeating a Balrog in the Second Age.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Arrives in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Lindir","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Council of Elrond","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"An Elf of Rivendell who spoke with Bilbo about his poem.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Servant"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed appreciation for Bilbo's poem and conversed with him about its elements."},{"name":"Arwen","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"Daughter of Elrond, pledged to Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Betrothed"}],"recentEvents":"Joined the merrymaking in the Hall of Fire and conversed with Elrond and Aragorn."},{"name":"Elrond Halfelven","aliases":["Lord Elrond","Lord of Rivendell"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"Elven lord of Rivendell, keeper of the Three Elven Rings, and host to the fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf the Grey","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Host and Patron for Long Time"}],"recentEvents":"Hosted a council to discuss the fate of the One Ring and named Frodo as the Ring-bearer."},{"name":"Faramir","aliases":["Faramir's Big Brother","captain","Captain of Gondor","Captain","Boromir","Faramir, son of Denethor","Prince of Ithilien"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Houses of Healing","description":"Faramir is the younger son of Denethor and the Captain of the Rangers of Ithilien.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Healed"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn advised the Warden to tend to Faramir in the Houses of Healing for many days."},{"name":"Legolas","aliases":["Greenleaf","Prince of Mirkwood","Elven Archer","Wood-elf","Legolas Greenleaf"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elven archer and member of the Fellowship, very capable in stealth and combat.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Travel companion and friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Travel companion"}],"recentEvents":"Departed singing, likely to walk in the woods of Ithilien."},{"name":"Gimli","aliases":["Son of Glóin","Dwarf","Gimli son of Glóin","Gimli the dwarf","Gimli Glóinsson"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Choices of Master Samwise","currentLocation":"Ithilien","description":"An axe-bearing dwarf and member of the Fellowship.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Fellow traveller and friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Travel companion"}],"recentEvents":"Partook in wine service and shared the recovery and growth of Pippin and Merry."},{"name":"Haldir","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Fangorn Forest","currentLocation":"Cerin Amroth","description":"A guard of Lothlórien who escorts Frodo and Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Guide to Lothlórien"}],"recentEvents":"Guided Frodo and Sam to Cerin Amroth and showed them the beauty of the place."},{"name":"Old Bent Man","aliases":["Old man with a hat"],"importance":"minor","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"In the chapter describing Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli's encounter","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An elderly man seen by Gimli near the fire at night. He disappeared shortly after appearing.","relationships":[{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Seen by"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Seen by"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Seen by"}],"recentEvents":"Appeared by the fire at night and frightened the travelers, then vanished."},{"name":"Théoden","aliases":["Third Marshal of the Mark","Rohan's Captain of the Mark, Lord of the Mark","Third Marshal of Rohan","Thorn, Hand of Rómendacil","First Marshal of the Mark","Prince of Rohan","Eomund's Second Son","Lord of the Mark","King of Rohan","Theoden","Eomund's son","Old King","King Théoden","Éomer","King Éomer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The King of Rohan who brings a large force to aid Gondor.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Imrahil","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Decides to march out with a force of seven thousand soldiers."},{"name":"Uglúk","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Uruk-Hai","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Leader of a raiding party sent by either Isengard or Mordor, not clearly identified in the text","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Killed by Éomer at the edge of Fangorn Forest"},{"name":"Treebeard","aliases":["The Ent","The Ward of the Forest","Bregalad","The Marching Ent","Treebeard the Ent","Fangorn"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Passing of the Grey Company","currentLocation":"Fangorn Forest","description":"A member of the Ents, an ancient race of shepherds and protectors of the forest, Treebeard is a tree-like creature with great wisdom and a deep connection to the land.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Pippin","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Legolas","relationship":"Recently met"},{"character":"Gimli","relationship":"Recently met"}],"recentEvents":"Treebeard discusses with Gandalf, Merry, Pippin, Legolas, and Gimli about Saruman's imprisonment in Orthanc and decides to keep a watch on him."},{"name":"Dernhelm","aliases":["Lady of Rohan","Éowyn"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Siege of Minas Tirith","currentLocation":"Houses of Healing","description":"Éowyn is the Shieldmaiden of Rohan and the niece of Théoden, King of Rohan.","relationships":[{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Healed and Honoured"}],"recentEvents":"Aragorn tended to her injuries and she is expected to remain in the Houses of Healing for several days."},{"name":"Háma","aliases":["Captain of the Guard"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The King of the Golden Hall","currentLocation":"Edoras","description":"The chief guard of Théoden's court.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"Guard"},{"character":"Éowyn","relationship":"Guard"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Guard"}],"recentEvents":"Names Éowyn as the ruler of Rohan during Théoden's absence."},{"name":"Erkenbrand","aliases":["Lord of Westfold"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Helm's Deep","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A lord of Rohan who joined the battle at Helm's Deep with his forces.","relationships":[{"character":"Théoden","relationship":"King and ally"}],"recentEvents":"Led his forces down the hills to defeat Isengard's forces at the Dike."},{"name":"Gríma Wormtongue","aliases":["Wormtongue","Master of Orthanc","Worm","Lurtz (in the films)"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Shire","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Saruman's servant who was responsible for poisoning the mind of Théoden King.","relationships":[{"character":"Saruman","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Killed Saruman at Frodo's mercy and then is killed himself by three hobbit-bows after attacking Frodo."},{"name":"Saruman","aliases":["the White Wizard","Gríma (in disguise)","Saruman of Many Colours","The White Wizard","Curunir"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The former head of the Order of Wizards, who was betrayed by his servant, Wormtongue, and later killed by him.","relationships":[{"character":"Wormtongue","relationship":"Servant"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Enemy"}],"recentEvents":"Saruman confronts Frodo outside Bag End and is ultimately killed by his servant, Wormtongue."},{"name":"Treebeard's Gatekeepers","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive",