rom Rohan.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle upon the field of Gondor."},{"name":"Harding","importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Knight from Rohan.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle upon the field of Gondor."},{"name":"Dûnhere","aliases":["Dúnhere"],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Knight from Rohan.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Fell in battle upon the field of Gondor."},{"name":"Imrahil","aliases":["Prince of Dol Amroth"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"The Prince of Dol Amroth who leads the defense of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Allies"},{"character":"Éomer","relationship":"Allies"}],"recentEvents":"Decides to march out with a force of seven thousand soldiers."},{"name":"Messenger of Mordor","importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Siege of Gondor","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A servant of Sauron who attempted to negotiate for Frodo's surrender","relationships":[{"character":"Sauron","relationship":"servant"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"opponent"}],"recentEvents":"Escaped the battle against Gandalf's power and returned to Mordor"},{"name":"Slave-Driving Orc","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Trapped at the Road's Edge","currentLocation":"Udûn","description":"A large orc with a whip who drives orc troops in Udûn","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Harasses and forces Frodo and Sam to join an orc march."},{"name":"Sauron","aliases":["the Dark Lord","the Eye"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Black Gate Opens","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The evil overlord who created the One Ring and seeks to dominate all of Middle-earth.","relationships":[{"character":"Sauron's servants","relationship":"commands and controls"}],"recentEvents":"The destruction of the One Ring caused his defeat and demise."},{"name":"Arwen Undómiel","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of the King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Daughter of Elrond and Evenstar of her people. Willing to become mortal for her love of Aragorn.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Fiancé and future wife"},{"character":"Elladan","relationship":"Brother"},{"character":"Elrohir","relationship":"Brother"}],"recentEvents":"Arrives in Minas Tirith and weds Aragorn."},{"name":"Erestor","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Return of the King","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"Advisor to Elrond, known for his wisdom.","relationships":[{"character":"Elrond","relationship":"Advisor to"}],"recentEvents":"Arrives in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Bill","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"unknown (prior to chapter)","currentLocation":"En Route to the Shire","description":"Sam's pony, stolen during their travels but unexpectedly returned to Bree.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Belonging; Sam is devoted to him."}],"recentEvents":"Returned to Bree and is now traveling with Sam."},{"name":"Rose Cotton","aliases":["Rose","Sam's wife"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Sam’s wife and a hobbit woman of the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed Sam back to Bywater with little Elanor."},{"name":"Elanor Gamgee","aliases":["Elanor","Lottle-lamb"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 5: The Grey Havens","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"The daughter of Sam and Rose Gamgee, named after her Aunt Lily.","relationships":[{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Rose Cotton","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Welcome home with her parents."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Shire","aliases":["Hobbiton","Shire"],"arc":"Journey and Return","description":"A pastoral land beloved by hobbits, known for its rolling hills and tranquil villages.","recentEvents":"The chapter concludes with Sam returning to the Shire, reflecting a sense of homecoming after his journey to the Grey Havens.","relationships":[{"location":"Bywater","relationship":"Bywater is a village within the Shire where Sam returns at the story's end."},{"location":"The Grey Havens","relationship":"The Grey Havens is the departure point for the final ride west."}]},{"name":"Bag End","aliases":["Bilbo's dwelling","Bilbo's residence","Bag-end, Mr. Bilbo's residence"],"arc":"Home","description":"Frodo's home in the Shire, known for its cozy interior and rich history. It was the place where the quest began and where Frodo plans to retire.","recentEvents":"Frodo confronts Saruman and Wormtongue at his home, leading to the death of both villains and the start of the Shire's recovery.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Located in the Shire, specifically in Hobbiton"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving Mathom-house","arc":"Shire History","description":"A museum and repository of historical artifacts in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Bilbo donated his coat of marvellous mail from his adventures to this institution.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"contains"}]},{"name":"Undertowers","arc":"Shire History","description":"The home of the Fairbairn family, an important Shire family. It houses the Red Book of Westmarch, a major historical source.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Great Smials","arc":"Shire History","description":"The major ancestral home of the Tooks, known for its extensive libraries containing historical records.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Bucklebury","aliases":["Buckland"],"arc":"Quest","description":"A region located east of the Brandywine River and connected to the Shire, known for its protective Hedge and resistance against foes.","recentEvents":"Mr. Baggins is planning to depart from Buckland under threat from Black Riders, with Fredegar Bolger staying behind.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Bordered by and connected to"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Adjacent to, with the Old Forest seen as a dangerous but necessary route"}]},{"name":"Rivendell","aliases":["Imladris"],"arc":"Return to the Shire","description":"A beautiful elven realm where Frodo receives important gifts and counsel before departing.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin bid farewell to Bilbo and receive various gifts. They also prepare to set off on their journey back to the Shire.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Frodo considers returning here to see Bilbo, but is discouraged from the idea"},{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Frodo and his companions will start their journey back here soon"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving","arc":"Shire History","description":"The chief town of the Shire, containing the Shire's major museums.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Minas Tirith","aliases":["White City","City of Gondor","The White City"],"arc":"Dominion of Men","description":"The White city and seat of kings in Gondor, symbol of the return of the rightful ruler and hope for a new age.","recentEvents":"King Elessar marries Arwen Undómiel, signifying the establishment of a new age and the rekindling of the White Tree.","relationships":[{"location":"Mount Mindolluin","relationship":"Mount where Aragorn finds the sapling of the White Tree"}]},{"name":"Gondor","arc":"Quest for the Ring","description":"A realm in conflict with Mordor, dedicated to the preservation of Men and the resistance against Sauron","recentEvents":"Faramir shows wisdom and restraint in his interactions with Frodo and Sam when they reveal the existence of the One Ring and their intentions to take it to Mordor.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothl³riën","relationship":"Lothl³riën and Gondor are both realms of Middle-earth allied against the threat of Sauron"}]},{"name":"Hellas","aliases":["Hellas Basin"],"arc":"Mars History","description":"A large, ancient impact crater on Mars known for its diverse geology and exploration in real-world scenarios, but not directly relevant to the narrative in this excerpt.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Bywater","arc":"The Quest","description":"A town in the Shire, known for its residents' gossip and suspicion.","recentEvents":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins left Bywater for Bag End, driving a pony-trap and carrying various items she had taken from the premises.","relationships":[{"location":"Bag End","relationship":"Adjacent to and highly connected with"}]},{"name":"Maggot's Farm","arc":"Escape","description":"A hobbit residence where Farmer Maggot and his family live, known for its hospitality and agricultural products such as mushrooms.","recentEvents":"Farmer Maggot provides shelter, assistance, and a wagon ride to Frodo and his friends at this location before the dark of night arrives.","relationships":[{"location":"Maggot's Lane","relationship":"The lane leads to his farm, where Frodo and his friends spend a brief time before traveling to the Ferry lane"},{"location":"Ferry Lane","relationship":"Located near the entrance to this strategic location"}]},{"name":"Old Forest","arc":"Misty","description":"A forest near Bree filled with sentient trees and ancient magic.","recentEvents":"The hobbits and Tom Bombadil have adventures near an old mound and encounter trees blocking their way.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjoins to the west"}]},{"name":"Barrow-downs","arc":"Journey","description":"A range of hills and burial mounds north of the Old Forest, known for resting sites of ancient kings and the haunting spirits of the dead.","recentEvents":"Tom cautions the Hobbits about avoiding the Barrows to prevent danger.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Directly northeast of the Old Forest, marking a significant northward travel point"}]},{"name":"Withywindle","aliases":["River","Brandywine"],"arc":"Withywindle","description":"The Withywindle river, flowing down to the Brandywine, offers a natural boundary and path.","recentEvents":"The characters leave the Old Forest and reach the riverbank before being led to Tom Bombadil’s house.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"The river serves as a clear border and escape route from the forest."},{"location":"Tom Bombadil’s House","relationship":"The river leads directly to Tom Bombadil’s abode."}]},{"name":"Tom Bombadil’s House","aliases":["House of Tom Bombadil"],"arc":"Withywindle","description":"Tom Bombadil’s sanctuary on the riverbank, symbolizing relief and safety.","recentEvents":"The characters are welcomed by Tom Bombadil after being rescued from the Old Forest.","relationships":[{"location":"Withywindle","relationship":"The house is located on the Withywindle riverbank, accessible after crossing the river."}]},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","aliases":["Tom's House"],"arc":"Journey","description":"A home in the Old Forest tended by Tom Bombadil and Goldberry, known for its hospitality and enchanting atmosphere.","recentEvents":"The Hobbits are entertained and informed here by Tom about their journey ahead.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Located near the Shire's outlying regions"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Inside the Old Forest, providing shelter and guidance"}]},{"name":"Bree","aliases":["Bree-village","under Bree-hill","village","Bree-town"],"arc":"The Journey Home","description":"A bustling town where strangers and locals gather freely; serves as a point between the Shire and other parts of Middle-earth.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions stay in Bree, where they rest and prepare for their return to the Shire. They have a final conversation with Mr. Butterbur before leaving.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Connected by the East Road; Bree is a major stopping point for travelers heading to and from the Shire."}]},{"name":"Bree-hill","arc":"Misty","description":"A prominent hill located to the west of Bree providing a view to the village nestled below it.","recentEvents":"The hobbits see Bree-hill rising against the stars and approach Bree as they journey towards it.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjoins and overlooks"}]},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","aliases":["inn","Barley's Inn"],"arc":"The Return of the Fellowship","description":"A popular pub and inn in Bree, known for its cheerful and friendly atmosphere.","recentEvents":"Hobbits Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin stay at the inn and face a night full of tension due to the lurking Black Riders.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Located within Bree and a key establishment for traveler accommodation."}]},{"name":"Weathertop","arc":"Journey","description":"A hill in the Northfarthing, notable for its peak which bears a stone cairn or ring.","recentEvents":"On Weathertop, Frodo and his companions are haunted by black shapes and face peril from supernatural beings while hiding in a dell.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Weathertop is located near the borders of The Shire and holds historical significance connected to Elendil and Isildur."},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"The journey from The Shire to Rivendell passes near Weathertop, making it an important milestone."}]},{"name":"Mordor","aliases":["The Land of Mordor","Black Land","Dark Land","The Land of Shadow"],"arc":"The Destruction of the Ring","description":"The land ruled by Sauron located east of Ithilien and west of Khand","recentEvents":"Upon the destruction of the One Ring in Mount Doom, Mordor experienced a massive earthquake and explosion, leading to the collapse of the Dark Tower and the apparent fall of Sauron.","relationships":[{"location":"Mount Doom","relationship":"Contains"},{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Opposite"},{"location":"Black Gate","relationship":"Boundary"}]},{"name":"Ford of Bruinen","arc":"Mordor","description":"A river ford near Rivendell where the River Bruinen flows across the road.","recentEvents":"Frodo and the Nine Black Riders confront each other here; a powerful spell by the river spirits prevents the Black Riders from crossing.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"The Black Riders aim to cross here to pursue Frodo back to"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Frodo crosses the river to safety here"}]},{"name":"Redhorn Gate","aliases":["Caradhras"],"arc":"Shadow Rising","description":"A high and dangerous mountain pass in the Misty Mountains, known for its treacherous weather and hostility to unwelcome travelers.","recentEvents":"The Company was trapped by a storm and forced to find a way through a massive snow drift to escape the pass.","relationships":[{"location":"Misty Mountains","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Moria","aliases":["Khazad-dûm","The Dwarrowdelf","Durin's Deep"],"arc":"The Quest for the Ring","description":"The ancient dwarf city and mine under the Misty Mountains, now abandoned and filled with orcs and evil creatures.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship fought a Balrog and Gandalf fell into the abyss. They escaped through the Great Gates and into Dimrill Dale.","relationships":[{"location":"The Misty Mountains","relationship":"Adjacent mountain range containing Moria"},{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Fellowship's previous destination before attempting Moria"},{"location":"Dimrill Dale","relationship":"Field outside the Moria Gates where the Fellowship emerged after escaping"}]},{"name":"Dimrill Dale","arc":"The Quest for the Ring","description":"A valley at the entrance of Moria, known for the Dimrill River which runs through it.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship emerged here after their escape from Moria and rested before grieving Gandalf's loss.","relationships":[{"location":"Moria","relationship":"Immediately adjacent and outside the Moria Gates"}]},{"name":"Lothl³riën","aliases":["Lórien","Lórinand","The Golden Wood","Land of the Galadhrim","Lorien","Lothlórien"],"arc":"Quest for the Ring","description":"A forest realm dedicated to the protection of the elves and the preservation of beauty","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam meet Faramir and disclose their mission and possession of the One Ring.","relationships":[{"location":"Gondor","relationship":"Lothl³riën and Gondor are both realms of Middle-earth allied against the threat of Sauron"}]},{"name":"Cerin Amroth","arc":"The Fellowship","description":"A sacred mound with ancient trees and winter flowers where the Fellowship rests in Lórien.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship climbs Cerin Amroth and finds a peaceful refuge with a view of the rest of Lórien and the ominous Dol Guldur across the river.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Part of the heartlands of Lórien"}]},{"name":"Dol Guldur","arc":"The Fellowship","description":"A dark, stony fortress hidden in Mirkwood forest across the Great River from Lórien.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship looks from Cerin Amroth and notices a dark cloud over Dol Guldur, indicating ongoing evil presence and potential reoccupation.","relationships":[{"location":"Lothlórien","relationship":"Across the Anduin River, opposing it with dark power"}]},{"name":"The Great River","aliases":["Anduin"],"arc":"The Quest for the Ring","description":"A major river serving as the dividing line between many regions and cultures in Middle-earth.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship travels down the river after leaving Lórien, experiencing a mix of awe and sorrow.","relationships":[{"location":"Lórien","relationship":"Merges with the Silverlode river"},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"Connected, though travel time not specified"}]},{"name":"Nen Hithoel","aliases":["Lake Nen Hithoel"],"arc":"Crossing to the West","description":"A wide, oval-shaped lake surrounded by steep, tree-clad hills and significant to ancient Númenórean history.","recentEvents":"The Fellowship passed through the Gates of Argonath and drifted into Nen Hithoel, encountering the three peaks of Amon Lhaw, Tol Brandir, and Amon Hen.","relationships":[{"location":"Emyn Muil","relationship":"Nen Hithoel is directly south of the Emyn Muil cliffs"},{"location":"Tol Brandir","relationship":"A central peak in Nen Hithoel"}]},{"name":"Tol Brandir","arc":"Departure of the Nine Companions","description":"An island located in the midst of Rauros falls on the Anduin river, surrounded by tumultuous rapids, known for its inaccessible nature and legend.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam use the western arm of the river to safely navigate past the island.","relationships":[{"location":"Nen Hithoel","relationship":"Tol Brandir is an island in the middle of Nen Hithoel"}]},{"name":"Amon Hen","aliases":["Seat of Amon Hen"],"arc":"Departure of the Nine Companions","description":"A high seat where one can see great distances to the south and west of the river Anduin, an important vantage point in Middle-earth","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam use this location to prepare for their departure to Mordor and hide the boat before setting off.","relationships":[{"location":"Parth Galen","relationship":"Frodo and Sam travel from Parth Galen to Amon Hen to hide their boat before departing."}]},{"name":"Parth Galen","aliases":["Lawn of Green Table"],"arc":"Quest","description":"A broad green lawn set by the banks of the River Anduin, where the Fellowship makes its crucial decision to split up.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam leave by boat to journey to Mordor, while Aragorn, Legolas, and Gimli decide to follow the Orcs who captured Merry and Pippin.","relationships":[{"location":"Emyn Muil","relationship":"Parth Galen is adjacent to and leads into Emyn Muil where the Orcs and the hunters head onward."}]},{"name":"Emyn Muil","arc":"Emyn Muil: The Fens and Marshes","description":"A vast and rugged region of mountains and marshes southeast of the Misty Mountains, forming a formidable natural barrier.","recentEvents":"Frodo and his companions were trapped in the Emyn Muil and were eventually guided by Gollum through the treacherous marshes.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Bounds part of eastern and southern border of Mordor"}]},{"name":"Fangorn Forest","aliases":["Fangorn","The Wild Wood"],"arc":"War of the Ring","description":"An ancient and powerful forest populated by Ents, sentient tree-like creatures, who become allies of the Fellowship","recentEvents":"Ents and their leader Treebeard agreed to assist Gandalf with keeping Saruman contained in Isengard. Treebeard offered the Hobbits a future visit to the forest.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Fangorn's trees surround Isengard, and its Ents are set to guard Saruman there."}]},{"name":"Rohan","aliases":["Mark"],"arc":"Rivendell to Isengard","description":"A kingdom of horsemen in northern Middle-earth, known for its cavalry and fierce martial prowess.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan engage in a battle against Orcs under Ugluk's leadership, culminating in the defeat of Ugluk.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"A neighboring realm in conflict with Isengard"},{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Fangorn borders the eastern borders of Rohan"}]},{"name":"Isengard","aliases":["Nan Curunír","Orthanc","Isengard's highest tower","Saruman's fortress"],"arc":"Treason","description":"Isengard is Saruman's fortress, a stronghold filled with immense power.","recentEvents":"Saruman's orc army raids Isengard, leading Gandalf and Pippin to infer that a Nazgûl messenger is dispatched to investigate.","relationships":[{"location":"Orthanc","relationship":"Contains"}]},{"name":"Meduseld","aliases":["Golden Hall","Edoras","City of the Golden Hall"],"arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"The capital city of Rohan, an important political and cultural center.","recentEvents":"King Théoden briefly stayed in Edoras to gather reinforcements before continuing his journey to aid Gondor.","relationships":[{"location":"Dunharrow","relationship":"Dunharrow is part of the territory and region of Rohan"}]},{"name":"Gap of Rohan","aliases":["Gap"],"arc":"Fellowship of the Ring","description":"Strategic mountain pass in Rohan.","recentEvents":"Smoke rises from the Gap, indicating that a battle is underway.","relationships":[{"location":"Isengard","relationship":"Guarded by Isengard against invasion"},{"location":"Fangorn Forest","relationship":"Adjacency to the east"}]},{"name":"White Mountains","arc":"Mordor Campaign","description":"The western mountain range that borders the fiefdoms of Gondor, serving as a natural barrier.","recentEvents":"Meduseld is located under its slopes.","relationships":[{"location":"Gondor","relationship":"Forming the western border of Gondor."}]},{"name":"Dunharrow","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A secret refuge and fortress carved into mountains, used by the Rohirrim for defense and shelter.","recentEvents":"King Théoden and his Riders departed from Dunharrow, beginning their journey to aid Gondor.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Dunharrow is part of the territory and region of Rohan"}]},{"name":"Helm's Deep","aliases":["Helm's Gate","Rohan's deep valley fortress"],"arc":"Rohan","description":"Helm's Deep is a fortress within the Western cliffs of Rohan, a defensive stronghold.","recentEvents":"Gandalf and Pippin plan to travel towards Helm's Deep but end up heading further south.","relationships":[{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Located in"}]},{"name":"Deeping Coomb","aliases":["Deeping Stream"],"arc":"Misty Mountains","description":"A valley located just beyond Helm's Deep, forming part of Rohan's eastern border defenses.","recentEvents":"Enemy forces were driven into the valley, where they were trapped and annihilated.","relationships":[{"location":"Helm's Deep","relationship":"Immediately adjacent and part of the same defensive system"}]},{"name":"Glittering Caves","aliases":["Aglarond"],"arc":"Rohan","description":"Glittering Caves are beautiful and vast caverns in the White Mountains of Rohan.","recentEvents":"Gandalf mentions that they will bypass the Glittering Caves during their journey.","relationships":[{"location":"Rohan","relationship":"Located in"}]},{"name":"The Dead Land","arc":"The Shadow Grows","description":"A desolate wasteland leading up to Mordor’s gate.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Sam, and Gollum experience fear and dread as they traverse this dangerous terrain.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"A part of Mordor leading up to the Gate"}]},{"name":"Barad-dûr","arc":"The Shadow Grows","description":"Sauron's stronghold, a looming dark tower that commands fear and reverence from his enemies.","recentEvents":"Signs of Barad-dûr’s power appear in the form of winged shapes overhead and a pervasive sense of dread.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Located within Mordor, the heart of Sauron's empire"}]},{"name":"Middle-earth","arc":"Mordor","description":"A vast and diverse realm containing many regions, cultures, and creatures.","recentEvents":"Sam and Frodo witness a battle between Men, involving the capture and subsequent escape of an Oliphaunt.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Part of the region facing the threat of Mordor"}]},{"name":"Cloven Way","arc":"Mordor","description":"A strategic passage used by armies, located near the border with Mordor.","recentEvents":"A group of Southrons was ambushed and defeated by Gondorian forces.","relationships":[{"location":"Mûmakil (Oliphaunt)","relationship":"The area where the Oliphaunt was encountered and escaped"}]},{"name":"Ithilien","aliases":["Vale of Minas Morgul"],"arc":"The War to Save Middle-earth","description":"A beautiful and enchanted forest and wild country between Mordor and Gondor, with hidden places like Henneth Annûn.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam rest and recover following the siege of Minas Tirith, spending time wandering Ithilien.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"East of Ithilien"},{"location":"Field of Cormallen","relationship":"Part of Ithilien, site of the Company's temporary encampment"}]},{"name":"Cross-roads","arc":"The Quest","description":"A significant junction where major roads intersect, located at the edge of the vast Ring of Isengard-like trees.","recentEvents":"The group has reached this junction at dusk, witnessing the setting sun and a fallen statue of a king with a crown placed mockingly on its remains.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Morgul","relationship":"Nearby and leading towards the Black Gate"},{"location":"Gondor","relationship":"Beyond the road leading to Osgiliath"}]},{"name":"Minas Morgul","description":"A dark and sinister tower in the eastern realm of Minas Ithil, now occupied by Sauron's forces.","recentEvents":"Frodo and Sam approach and pass by Minas Morgul on their journey.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Minas Morgul is on the borders of Mordor, at the foot of the Ephel Dúath mountains."}]},{"name":"Shelob's Lair","arc":"Journey: Mordor","description":"A dark cave inhabited by Shelob, the great spider, where Frodo is attacked and poisoned.","recentEvents":"Frodo is poisoned by Shelob but survives and is taken as a prisoner."},{"name":"Tower of Cirith Ungol","aliases":["Tower","Cirith Ungol"],"arc":"Escape from Cirith Ungol","description":"A fortified tower in the high pass of Cirith Ungol watching the road to Mordor","recentEvents":"Frodo is rescued from captivity by Sam after a brief skirmish between Sam and the orc-guard, and they escape out of the gate.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"It lies on the border of the dark land"},{"location":"Mount Doom","relationship":"Frodo and Sam must now navigate through this land towards their destination"}]},{"name":"Morthond Vale","description":"A deep, narrow valley with steep slopes that serve as a main pass to Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Grey Company rode through Morthond Vale, causing panic among the local population due to the rumor of the King of the Dead's approach.","relationships":[{"location":"Blackroot River (Morthond)","relationship":"Runs through"},{"location":"Erech","relationship":"Nexus of the Dead's oath fulfillment"}]},{"name":"Hill of Erech","description":"A hill with a black stone that stands as a symbol of dread and legend for the local inhabitants.","recentEvents":"Aragorn summoned the Dead Men at this location to fulfill their ancient oath.","relationships":[{"location":"Dunharrow","relationship":"Point of origin for Aragorn's summons"},{"location":"Pelargir","relationship":"Destination for Aragorn's forces after oath fulfillment"}]},{"name":"River Snowbourn","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A significant waterway in Rohan, important for both military and agricultural purposes.","recentEvents":"The King and his Riders crossed the Snowbourn, continuing their ride in increasing gloom.","relationships":[{"location":"Dunharrow","relationship":"Flows near Dunharrow"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Flows near Edoras"}]},{"name":"Halifirien","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A significant landmark on the borders of Rohan and Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan rode past Halifirien on the march, experiencing increasing signs of war approaching their borders.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Near Edoras"}]},{"name":"Entwash","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A great river that flows across Rohan and through marshlands.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan rode around Entwash’s marshes, continuing their journey to aid Gondor.","relationships":[{"location":"River Snowbourn","relationship":"Meets Snowbourn"},{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Flows near Edoras"}]},{"name":"Folde","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A region of Rohan lying east of Edoras through which the River Snowbourn flows.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan passed through Folde on their way to Gondor.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"East of Edoras"}]},{"name":"Fenmarch","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A marshy region along the borders of Rohan and Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan rode through Fenmarch on their way to aid Gondor, encountering rumors of orc-hosts marching in the Wold of Rohan.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"Near Edoras"}]},{"name":"Min-Rimmon","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A beacon hill located in Rohan near the borders of Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan passed by Min-Rimmon, one of the beacon hills, during their journey towards Gondor, though its fire was unlit.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"North of Edoras"},{"location":"Halifirien","relationship":"Near Halifirien"}]},{"name":"Erelas","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A beacon hill located in Rohan near the borders of Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan passed by Erelas, one of the beacon hills, during their journey towards Gondor, though its fire was unlit.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"North of Edoras"},{"location":"Halifirien","relationship":"Near Halifirien"}]},{"name":"Nardol","arc":"The Ride to Gondor","description":"A beacon hill situated along the borders of Rohan and Gondor.","recentEvents":"The Riders of Rohan passed by Nardol, one of the beacon hills, during their journey towards Gondor, though its fire was unlit.","relationships":[{"location":"Edoras","relationship":"North of Edoras"},{"location":"Halifirien","relationship":"Near Halifirien"}]},{"name":"Anórien","arc":"Battle For Minas Tirith","description":"The region east of Minas Tirith which includes part of Gondor's eastern borderlands.","recentEvents":"The army of Rohan crosses through Anórien to reach Minas Tirith during the battle.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Anórien borders Minas Tirith and serves as a route for Rohan's troops to travel to the city"}]},{"name":"Rammas","arc":"Battle For Minas Tirith","description":"The outer defenses of Minas Tirith, a wall encircling the city in Anórien.","recentEvents":"Rohan's army breaches the Rammas where the wall has been destroyed or abandoned.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"The Rammas is the outermost defense of Minas Tirith"},{"location":"Anórien","relationship":"The Rammas follows the boundary of Anórien to shield Minas Tirith"}]},{"name":"Pelennor Fields","aliases":["fields of Gondor"],"arc":"War of the Ring","description":"A vast open area surrounding the city of Minas Tirith, used as pastureland and the site of significant battles.","recentEvents":"The Battle of the Pelennor Fields commenced with a cry that signified the destruction of the captain of the enemy's forces. It marked a turning point in the war.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Adjacent and where the battle was fought"}]},{"name":"Harlond","arc":"Mordor Campaign","description":"A harbor area near Minas Tirith along the Anduin River, where ships and troops are gathered to support the defense of the city.","recentEvents":"Ships and troops are being gathered here to support the defensive effort around Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Eastern harbors of Minas Tirith along the Anduin River."}]},{"name":"Houses of Healing","arc":"War of the Ring","description":"A sanctuary within Minas Tirith designated for the care of the injured and sick, prepared to handle those harmed in battle or on the brink of death.","recentEvents":"Faramir, critically injured, was taken to the Houses of Healing by Gandalf and Beregond.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Rath Dínen","aliases":["Dead Men's Street"],"arc":"War of the Ring","description":"A street or district within Minas Tirith associated with burials and the dead.","recentEvents":"The house of Denethor, the steward, was consumed by a fiery collapse following his fiery suicide.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Pelargir","arc":"Mordor Campaign","description":"A city and port on the southern coast of Gondor, now freed from the rule of Sauron.","recentEvents":"Four thousand men from the southern fiefs, led by Angbor, march to Pelargir to support Gondor’s defense against Mordor.","relationships":[{"location":"Gondor","relationship":"Part of the kingdom of Gondor."},{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Northern base of operations for the soldiers marching from Pelargir."}]},{"name":"Lossarnach","arc":"Mordor Campaign","description":"A fertile region between the White Mountains and the lands of Anórien and Ithilien.","recentEvents":"The route taken by Aragorn’s reinforcements from the southern fiefs, marching northward to join the defense of Minas Tirith.","relationships":[{"location":"Pelargir","relationship":"Southern border of Lossarnach."},{"location":"Anórien","relationship":"Northern border of Lossarnach."}]},{"name":"Black Gate (Cirith Gorgor)","aliases":["Morannon","Cirith Gorgor"],"arc":"Battle and Destruction","description":"The primary entrance to Mordor guarded by the Towers of the Teeth.","recentEvents":"Sauron opens the Black Gate for a grand assault after his trap is sprung by the forces of the West.","relationships":[{"location":"Cirith Ungol","relationship":"Adjacent pass used by orcs and others entering Mordor."},{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Guarded entrance to the land of Mordor."}]},{"name":"Ered Lithui","arc":"Battle and Destruction","description":"Mountain range bordering the Plateau of Gorgoroth.","recentEvents":"Mordor's Easterling forces lay in wait near Ered Lithui to join the attack on the forces of the West.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Range within Mordor, home to forces waiting to assist Sauron's assault."},{"location":"Black Gate","relationship":"Nearby mountains where forces lie before joining the battle at Black Gate."}]},{"name":"Tower of Guard","arc":"Battle and Destruction","description":"Tower in Minas Tirith.","recentEvents":"Men from the Tower of Guard fight in the battle near the Black Gate.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Part of the city where some defenders come from."}]},{"name":"Dol Amroth","arc":"Hero's Journey","description":"City on the coast of Lebennin.","recentEvents":"Men from Dol Amroth fight near the Black Gate.","relationships":[{"location":"Lebennin","relationship":"Located on the coast of Lebennin in Gondor."},{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Defenders join allies near the Black Gate."}]},{"name":"Mount Doom","aliases":["The Mountain","Orodruin"],"arc":"The Destruction of the Ring","description":"A volcanic mountain within Mordor where the One Ring was forged and can be destroyed","recentEvents":"Frodo placed the Ring on his finger, Gollum seized it and fell into the fiery chasm, causing a massive explosion and sending Nazgûl in a futile attempt to retrieve it.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Part of the geography"}]},{"name":"Udûn","description":"The deep, dark valley leading up to Mordor from the southern mountains","recentEvents":"Hobbits follow orc forces through Udûn to escape notice and avoid capture.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"Part of Mordor"},{"location":"Mount Doom","relationship":"Proximity to the volcanic region where Frodo plans to destroy the Ring"}]},{"name":"Henneth Annûn","arc":"The War to Save Middle-earth","description":"A hidden secret grotto and falls in the cliff with a concealed pool, part of Ithilien.","recentEvents":"Notable only as a former stopping place of the Hobbits","relationships":[{"location":"Ithilien","relationship":"Part of the eastern wilderness"}]},{"name":"Cair Andros","arc":"The War to Save Middle-earth","description":"A great island between the eastern and western halves of Gondor, significant as a strategic crossing point.","recentEvents":"The host remained briefly there before departing to Osgiliath and then the Pelennor Fields.","relationships":[{"location":"Gondor","relationship":"North of Minas Tirith, at the Anduin river's center"}]},{"name":"Mount Mindolluin","arc":"Dominion of Men","description":"A mountain south of Minas Tirith where Aragorn finds the sapling of the White Tree, symbolizing a sign from the past.","recentEvents":"Aragorn and Gandalf climb the mountain, where Aragorn discovers a sapling of the White Tree, symbolizing a new beginning.","relationships":[{"location":"Minas Tirith","relationship":"Location directly south of the White City where the sapling was found"}]},{"name":"The Grey Havens","arc":"Journey and Return","description":"A port city at the edge of Middle-earth where Elves depart for Valinor.","recentEvents":"Frodo, Bilbo, and Gandalf depart from the Grey Havens for the Undying Lands, leaving Sam and his friends behind.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"The Havens lie at the eastern edge of the Shire, serving as the departure point for Middle-earth's inhabitants bound for Valinor."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Frodo and Sam Journey to Mordor","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam"],"summary":"Frodo and Sam continue their perilous journey through Mordor, facing capture and conscription into the Dark Lord's army before escaping into the plain."},{"name":"Return to Minas Tirith","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam","Gandalf","Legolas","Gimli","Pippin","Merry","Éomer","Imrahil","Aragorn"],"summary":"The group has spent time in Ithilien, healing and recounting their individual journeys, with a plan to return to Minas Tirith for Aegnor's coronation."},{"name":"Rebuilding and Restoration of Gondor","status":"active","characters":["Aragorn","Gandalf","Elladan","Elrohir"],"summary":"With the destruction of the One Ring, Gondor is on the path to restoration, including the planting of a sapling from the White Tree of Gondor."},{"name":"Reunions and Farewells","status":"active","characters":["Frodo Baggins","Gandalf","Elrond","Galadriel"],"summary":"The Elves and other key characters gather in Minas Tirith at the Eve of Midsummer for Arwen's wedding and to mark the end of the Third Age."},{"name":"Quest to Destroy the One Ring","status":"active","characters":["Frodo Baggins","Samwise Gamgee","Merry Brandybuck","Pippin Took","Bilbo Baggins","Gandalf"],"summary":"Frodo and his companions prepare to leave Rivendell for their journey back to the Shire, with Gandalf rejoining them until Bree."},{"name":"Saruman's Influence on the Shire","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam","Merry","Pippin","Gandalf"],"summary":"Gandalf warns the hobbits that Saruman's influence extends to the Shire, setting the stage for potential conflicts upon their return."},{"name":"Rebuilding of the Shire","status":"active","characters":["Frodo Baggins","Samwise Gamgee","Meriadoc Brandybuck","Peregrin Took"],"summary":"With the destruction of Sauron, the four hobbits turn their attention to restoring the Shire from the ruins left by Saruman and his men."},{"name":"Life in the Shire","status":"active","characters":["Sam","Rose","Elanor"],"summary":"Sam returns to the Shire, reflecting contentment as he reunites with his family and reestablishes life in the Shire."}],"summary":"After a perilous journey, Frodo and Bilbo bid farewell to Sam, Merry, and Pippin at the Grey Havens, where they depart for the Undying Lands. Sam returns to the Shire, marking the end of a tale filled with sacrifice and friendship."},"snapshots":[{"index":6,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Burglar","Master Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Mr. Baggins' Journey","currentLocation":"Bag End, The Shire","description":"A hobbit who became a reluctant adventurer through his acquisition of the One Ring, returned home to the Shire after his journey, and kept the Ring secret.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Mentor and confidant"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"}],"recentEvents":"Celebrated his 111th birthday before settling down to write about his adventures, keeping the Red Book as a private diary."},{"name":"Gandalf","aliases":["the grey wizard"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Mr. Baggins' Journey","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A wizard who leads the fight against Sauron and maintains interest in Bilbo's possessions.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Mentor and confidant"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Questioned Bilbo about the ring, becoming suspicious of his secrecy."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Mr. Underhill"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Mr. Baggins' Journey","currentLocation":"The Shire","description":"Bilbo's heir and a hobbit who inherits and sets out to destroy the One Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend and guide"}],"recentEvents":"Inherited the Red Book and the One Ring from Bilbo."},{"n