adriel."},{"name":"Barahir","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Gondor","description":"Grandson of the Steward Faramir, author of the abbreviated version of The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Wrote The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen for the history of Gondor."},{"name":"Findegil","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King's Writer who completed the Thain's Book.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Completed a copy of the Red Book in Minas Tirith."}],"locations":[{"name":"Shire","aliases":["The Shire"],"arc":"Shire History","description":"A peaceful, rural region of Middle-earth ruled over by Hobbits, known for its lush farmlands and cozy hobbit-holes.","recentEvents":"Mr. Baggins begins preparing for his hundred-and-eleventh birthday celebration, during which the narrative officially commences.","relationships":[{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"connected by road to"},{"location":"Michel Delving Mathom-house","relationship":"contains"}]},{"name":"Bag End","arc":"Shire History","description":"Bilbo and Frodo Baggins' home in Hobbiton, a cozy hole with a door that reads 'Bag End'.","recentEvents":"Bilbo returns home after his adventures and keeps the rare and mysterious ring in his pocket for many years.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving Mathom-house","arc":"Shire History","description":"A museum and repository of historical artifacts in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Bilbo donated his coat of marvellous mail from his adventures to this institution.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"contains"}]},{"name":"Undertowers","arc":"Shire History","description":"The home of the Fairbairn family, an important Shire family. It houses the Red Book of Westmarch, a major historical source.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},