ossesses the power to repel the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guided by him"}],"recentEvents":"Guided and protected the hobbits from the Black Riders, leading them back to the Road and to the village of Bree."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Queen of the River"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"House near the village of Stock","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she is known as the Queen of the River and is believed to have some magical or mystical powers associated with water.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippen","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed the hobbits, served them a supper and sang songs."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butler","Barley"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Landlord of The Prancing Pony and supplier of rumors.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Landlord"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Regular patron"}],"recentEvents":"Dealt with the confusion caused by Frodo's sudden disappearance."},{"name":"Strider","aliases":["Aragorn","Thorongil","Dúnadan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Knife in the Dark","currentLocation":"Weathertop","description":"A Ranger and descendant of Elendil, tasked with protecting the hobbits from the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guide and protector"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"}],"recentEvents":"Strider rushed towards the Ringwraiths brandishing flaming brands upon discovering them near Frodo."},{"name":"Mugwort","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","last_seen":"Strider","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"A local Hobbit who witnessed Frodo's vanishing act.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Asserted he saw Frodo vanish into thin air, causing an uproar."},{"name":"Nob","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"An inn servant who helps Frodo and his companions.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"servant and confidant"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"servant and confidant"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"servant and confidant"}],"recentEvents":"Nob assists in the preparation and safety arrangements of the hobbits' rooms at the Prancing Pony Inn."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Shire","aliases":["Hobbiton","Shire"],"arc":"Journey","description":"A quiet, pastoral land known for its contented hobbits and rolling countryside.","recentEvents":"The Hobbits have left the Shire and met Tom Bombadil near the borders.","relationships":[{"location":"Riverdale","relationship":"Tom Bombadil is a frequent visitor here"},{"location":"Hobbiton","relationship":"Close to the Shire's heart, where the Hobbits originated"}]},{"name":"Bag End","aliases":["Bilbo's dwelling","Bilbo's residence","Bag-end, Mr. Bilbo's residence"],"arc":"Quest for the Ring","description":"The home of Bilbo and later Frodo Baggins, a well-known hobbit hole in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Frodo has a discussion with Gandalf about the peril of the Ring and his need to leave.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Part of the larger Shire region where hobbits live"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving Mathom-house","arc":"Shire History","description":"A museum and repository of historical artifacts in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Bilbo donated his coat of marvellous mail from his adventures to this institution.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"contains"}]},{"name":"Undertowers","arc":"Shire History","description":"The home of the Fairbairn family, an important Shire family. It houses the Red Book of Westmarch, a major historical source.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Great Smials","arc":"Shire History","description":"The major ancestral home of the Tooks, known for its extensive libraries containing historical records.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Bucklebury","aliases":["Buckland"],"arc":"Quest","description":"A region located east of the Brandywine River and connected to the Shire, known for its protective Hedge and resistance against foes.","recentEvents":"Mr. Baggins is planning to depart from Buckland under threat from Black Riders, with Fredegar Bolger staying behind.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Bordered by and connected to"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Adjacent to, with the Old Forest seen as a dangerous but necessary route"}]},{"name":"Rivendell","aliases":["Imladris"],"arc":"Homecoming and Departure","description":"A haven of Elvish wisdom and safety in the mountains.","recentEvents":"Frodo plans to travel there seeking refuge and counsel, but now his journey has become urgent and perilous.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"connected by road to"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving","arc":"Shire History","description":"The chief town of the Shire, containing the Shire's major museums.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Minas Tirith","arc":"Gondor History","description":"The White City, capital of Gondor and a fortress on the edge of the Anduin Valley.","recentEvents":"A copy of the Red Book was made here at the request of King Elessar.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"connected by road to"}]},{"name":"Gondor","arc":"Gondor History","description":"A kingdom of Men in Middle-earth south of the Shire, rich in history and lore.","recentEvents":"A copy of the Thain's Book was made in Gondor.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"connected by road to"}]},{"name":"Hellas","aliases":["Hellas Basin"],"arc":"Mars History","description":"A large, ancient impact crater on Mars known for its diverse geology and exploration in real-world scenarios, but not directly relevant to the narrative in this excerpt.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Bywater","arc":"The Quest","description":"A town in the Shire, known for its residents' gossip and suspicion.","recentEvents":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins left Bywater for Bag End, driving a pony-trap and carrying various items she had taken from the premises.","relationships":[{"location":"Bag End","relationship":"Adjacent to and highly connected with"}]},{"name":"Maggot's Farm","arc":"Escape","description":"A hobbit residence where Farmer Maggot and his family live, known for its hospitality and agricultural products such as mushrooms.","recentEvents":"Farmer Maggot provides shelter, assistance, and a wagon ride to Frodo and his friends at this location before the dark of night arrives.","relationships":[{"location":"Maggot's Lane","relationship":"The lane leads to his farm, where Frodo and his friends spend a brief time before traveling to the Ferry lane"},{"location":"Ferry Lane","relationship":"Located near the entrance to this strategic location"}]},{"name":"Old Forest","arc":"Misty","description":"A forest near Bree filled with sentient trees and ancient magic.","recentEvents":"The hobbits and Tom Bombadil have adventures near an old mound and encounter trees blocking their way.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjoins to the west"}]},{"name":"Barrow-downs","arc":"Journey","description":"A range of hills and burial mounds north of the Old Forest, known for resting sites of ancient kings and the haunting spirits of the dead.","recentEvents":"Tom cautions the Hobbits about avoiding the Barrows to prevent danger.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Directly northeast of the Old Forest, marking a significant northward travel point"}]},{"name":"Withywindle","aliases":["River","Brandywine"],"arc":"Withywindle","description":"The Withywindle river, flowing down to the Brandywine, offers a natural boundary and path.","recentEvents":"The characters leave the Old Forest and reach the riverbank before being led to Tom Bombadil’s house.","relationships":[{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"The river serves as a clear border and escape route from the forest."},{"location":"Tom Bombadil’s House","relationship":"The river leads directly to Tom Bombadil’s abode."}]},{"name":"Tom Bombadil’s House","aliases":["House of Tom Bombadil"],"arc":"Withywindle","description":"Tom Bombadil’s sanctuary on the riverbank, symbolizing relief and safety.","recentEvents":"The characters are welcomed by Tom Bombadil after being rescued from the Old Forest.","relationships":[{"location":"Withywindle","relationship":"The house is located on the Withywindle riverbank, accessible after crossing the river."}]},{"name":"Tom Bombadil's House","aliases":["Tom's House"],"arc":"Journey","description":"A home in the Old Forest tended by Tom Bombadil and Goldberry, known for its hospitality and enchanting atmosphere.","recentEvents":"The Hobbits are entertained and informed here by Tom about their journey ahead.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Located near the Shire's outlying regions"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Inside the Old Forest, providing shelter and guidance"}]},{"name":"Bree","aliases":["Bree-village","under Bree-hill","village"],"arc":"The Return of the Fellowship","description":"A small village at a crossroads where the road from the Shire meets the main West Road from Eriador. It is a common stop for travelers between Bree and the Shire.","recentEvents":"Black Riders are suspected to be lurking around Bree, leading to increased tension among the residents. A hobbit, Merry, nearly encounters one of these strange beings.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Neighboring region that many travelers pass through on the way to Bree."},{"location":"East Road","relationship":"Main road that runs through Bree and connects it to other regions of Eriador."}]},{"name":"Bree-hill","arc":"Misty","description":"A prominent hill located to the west of Bree providing a view to the village nestled below it.","recentEvents":"The hobbits see Bree-hill rising against the stars and approach Bree as they journey towards it.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Adjoins and overlooks"}]},{"name":"The Prancing Pony","aliases":["inn","Barley's Inn"],"arc":"The Return of the Fellowship","description":"A popular pub and inn in Bree, known for its cheerful and friendly atmosphere.","recentEvents":"Hobbits Frodo, Sam, Merry, and Pippin stay at the inn and face a night full of tension due to the lurking Black Riders.","relationships":[{"location":"Bree","relationship":"Located within Bree and a key establishment for traveler accommodation."}]},{"name":"Weathertop","arc":"Journey","description":"A hill in the Northfarthing, notable for its peak which bears a stone cairn or ring.","recentEvents":"On Weathertop, Frodo and his companions are haunted by black shapes and face peril from supernatural beings while hiding in a dell.","relationships":[{"location":"The Shire","relationship":"Weathertop is located near the borders of The Shire and holds historical significance connected to Elendil and Isildur."},{"location":"Rivendell","relationship":"The journey from The Shire to Rivendell passes near Weathertop, making it an important milestone."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Frodo's Journey","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam","Merry","Pippin","Tom Bombadil"],"summary":"Frodo and the hobbits leave the Old Forest, encountering Tom Bombadil who guides them back to the Road. Now they journey towards Bree, wary of Black Riders potentially lying in wait."},{"name":"Meeting Tom Bombadil","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam","Pippin","Merry","Tom Bombadil","Goldberry"],"summary":"Tom Bombadil and Goldberry host the hobbits, revealing their mystical knowledge and capabilities. Tom teaches the Ring is powerless against him."},{"name":"The Journey to Rivendell","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Sam","Pippin","Merry"],"summary":"The hobbits are preparing to leave Tom's house, with Tom advising them on the road ahead and cautionary advice on Barrow-wights."},{"name":"The Bree Encounter","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Strider","Barliman Butterbur"],"summary":"Frodo's mysterious vanishing act has caused confusion and suspicion among the townspeople of Bree, prompting Butterbur to seek out a private conversation with him and Strider to further address the implications of Frodo's sudden disappearance."},{"name":"The Ranger's Role","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Strider"],"summary":"Strider's growing interest in Frodo and the unusual occurrences surrounding him has intensified. Frodo is aware that a private conversation with Strider is imminent, and he begins to suspect that Strider could be more involved than he initially believed."},{"name":"Gandalf's Missing","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Merry","Pippin","Strider"],"summary":"The disappearance of Gandalf remains concerning and mysterious, with Strider revealing the Riders' likely knowledge of the hobbits' presence."},{"name":"Black Riders' Threat","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Merry","Pippin","Strider"],"summary":"The Black Riders have been sighted near Bree, posing an imminent threat and tightening the circle around the hobbits."},{"name":"Pursuit and Confrontation on Weathertop","status":"active","characters":["Frodo","Strider","Merry","Pippin","Sam"],"summary":"Strider confronts Black Riders near Weathertop, with Frodo's desperate struggle against the temptation to use the Ring."}],"summary":"Frodo and his three hobbit companions are sheltering in a dell on Weathertop at night when they encounter supernatural beings in black cloaks and helms. Frodo faces a powerful urge to put on the Ring, and when he does, he sees their true forms as menacing sword-wielding figures. After a brief struggle, he passes out from a stab wound as Strider arrives to engage the attackers."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":19,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Bilbo Baggins","aliases":["Burglar","Master Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Mr. Baggins' Journey","currentLocation":"Bag End, The Shire","description":"A hobbit who became a reluctant adventurer through his acquisition of the One Ring, returned home to the Shire after his journey, and kept the Ring secret.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Mentor and confidant"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Nephew and heir"}],"recentEvents":"Celebrated his 111th birthday before settling down to write about his adventures, keeping the Red Book as a private diary."},{"name":"Gandalf","aliases":["the grey wizard","Gandalf the Grey"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Long-Expected Party","currentLocation":"Bag End","description":"A wizard and mentor to Frodo","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"protector and guide"},{"character":"Sam Gamgee","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Frodo about the dangers of the One Ring and the approach of the Enemy, suggested that Frodo leave the Shire, exposed Sam Gamgee as an eavesdropper."},{"name":"Frodo Baggins","aliases":["Mr. Underhill","Samwise's master","Elf-friend","Mr. Baggins","Frodo","The Ring-bearer","Underhill","Frodo, The Ring-bearer"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"At the Ford of Bruinen","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A Hobbit from the Shire with the burden of carrying the One Ring to destroy it.","relationships":[{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Fellow Ring-bearer and friend"},{"character":"Gollum","relationship":"Former Ring-bearer and shadowy follower"}],"recentEvents":"Frodo confronted nine Black Riders at the Ford of Bruinen. He attempted to stand against them and was nearly captured when he was rescued by a sudden flood sent by Glorfindel."},{"name":"Peregrin Took","aliases":["Pippin","Mr. Pippin Took","Peregrin","Mr. Took","Pippin Took"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Knife in the Dark","currentLocation":"Weathertop","description":"A young hobbit and friend of Merry's, who joins the journey from the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":" Cousin and friend"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"}],"recentEvents":"Pippin grew terrified and fell flat to the ground when the Black Riders charged."},{"name":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","aliases":["Merry","Master","Master Merry","Meriadoc","Mr. Brandybuck","Merry Brandybuck"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Knife in the Dark","currentLocation":"Weathertop","description":"A young hobbit and friend of Frodo's, who joins the journey from the Shire.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":" Cousin and friend"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"}],"recentEvents":"Merry saw the black figures approaching and shrank with fear during the attack."},{"name":"Elrond","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Rivendell","description":"High Elf and Lord of Rivendell who has held councils and meetings about Sauron.","relationships":[{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Host in Rivendell"},{"character":"Gandalf","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Held the last living memory of the Elder Days in Rivendell."},{"name":"Galadriel","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Lórien","description":"Elven Queen who gave gifts to the Fellowship of the Ring.","relationships":[{"character":"Celeborn","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Departed from Middle-earth to the Undying Lands."},{"name":"Celeborn","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Lórien","description":"Elven Lord of Lórien and husband of Galadriel.","relationships":[{"character":"Galadriel","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Noted only as living in Lórien with Galadriel."},{"name":"Barahir","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Gondor","description":"Grandson of the Steward Faramir, author of the abbreviated version of The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Wrote The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen for the history of Gondor."},{"name":"Findegil","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King's Writer who completed the Thain's Book.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Completed a copy of the Red Book in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Sackville-Baggins family, rival of the Baggins family, known for her jealousy and desire to inherit Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"Husband"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Rival"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Antagonist"}],"recentEvents":"Visited Frodo and pestered him about Bilbo's will, accusing him of being a Brandybuck."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Samwise","Sam Gamgee"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Knife in the Dark","currentLocation":"Weathertop","description":"Frodo's loyal servant and friend, accompanies the Ring-bearer on his quest.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Servant and friend"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Friend and companion"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Protector of Frodo"}],"recentEvents":"Sam stayed close to Frodo during the encounter with the Ringwraiths."},{"name":"Gildor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elf who encountered Frodo and his companions, giving them guidance and warning of peril.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met and gave advice to"}],"recentEvents":"Met Frodo and gave him warnings about enemies and advised him to take friends with him."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire known for his dogs and mushrooms.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Provided hospitality and transportation to the Ring-bearers."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty Bolger"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: Three is Company","currentLocation":"Crickhollow","description":"A hobbit from the Eastfarthing with an aversion to travel who was tasked with staying behind to deceive potential trackers.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to stay behind to pretend Frodo was still at Crickhollow."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil","aliases":["None","Master of the Green Path","Iarwain Ben-Adar","Master of Lake and Wood","Master of Many Songs"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mysterious man of the forest who lives in the lands near the Shire. He possesses the power to repel the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guided by him"}],"recentEvents":"Guided and protected the hobbits from the Black Riders, leading them back to the Road and to the village of Bree."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Queen of the River"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"House near the village of Stock","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she is known as the Queen of the River and is believed to have some magical or mystical powers associated with water.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippen","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed the hobbits, served them a supper and sang songs."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butler","Barley"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Landlord of The Prancing Pony and supplier of rumors.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Landlord"},{"character":"Strider","relationship"