tion":"A gardener and loyal friend of Frodo; has accompanied Frodo to Rivendell.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Gardener and Best Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Spoke up to support Frodo's decision to take the Ring, to ensure Frodo wouldn't go alone."},{"name":"Gildor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elf who encountered Frodo and his companions, giving them guidance and warning of peril.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Met and gave advice to"}],"recentEvents":"Met Frodo and gave him warnings about enemies and advised him to take friends with him."},{"name":"Farmer Maggot","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Shadow of the Past","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A farmer in the Shire known for his dogs and mushrooms.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Former enemy turned friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Provided hospitality and transportation to the Ring-bearers."},{"name":"Fredegar Bolger","aliases":["Fatty Bolger"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3: Three is Company","currentLocation":"Crickhollow","description":"A hobbit from the Eastfarthing with an aversion to travel who was tasked with staying behind to deceive potential trackers.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Meriadoc Brandybuck","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Peregrin Took","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Agreed to stay behind to pretend Frodo was still at Crickhollow."},{"name":"Tom Bombadil","aliases":["None","Master of the Green Path","Iarwain Ben-Adar","Master of Lake and Wood","Master of Many Songs"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mysterious man of the forest who lives in the lands near the Shire. He possesses the power to repel the Black Riders.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Samwise Gamgee","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Merry Brandybuck","relationship":"Guided by him"},{"character":"Pippin Took","relationship":"Guided by him"}],"recentEvents":"Guided and protected the hobbits from the Black Riders, leading them back to the Road and to the village of Bree."},{"name":"Goldberry","aliases":["Queen of the River"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"House near the village of Stock","description":"The wife of Tom Bombadil, she is known as the Queen of the River and is believed to have some magical or mystical powers associated with water.","relationships":[{"character":"Tom Bombadil","relationship":"Spouse"},{"character":"Merry","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Pippen","relationship":"Guest"},{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Guest"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed the hobbits, served them a supper and sang songs."},{"name":"Barliman Butterbur","aliases":["Mr. Butler","Barley"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Strider","currentLocation":"The Prancing Pony","description":"Landlord of The Prancing Pony and supplier of rumors.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Landlord"},{"character":"Strider","relationship":"Regular patron"}],"recentEvents":"Dealt with the confusion caused by Frodo's sudden disappearance."},{"name":"Aragorn","aliases":["Thorongil","Dúnadan","Strider","Elessar"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Farewell to Lórien","currentLocation":"Imladris (Rivendell)","description":"A Dúnadan and heir to the kingdom of Gondor, later known as Elessar Telcontar after becoming King.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Guided him to Rivendell"},{