 home of Bilbo and later Frodo Baggins, a well-known hobbit hole in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Frodo has a discussion with Gandalf about the peril of the Ring and his need to leave.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Part of the larger Shire region where hobbits live"}]},{"name":"Michel Delving Mathom-house","arc":"Shire History","description":"A museum and repository of historical artifacts in the Shire.","recentEvents":"Bilbo donated his coat of marvellous mail from his adventures to this institution.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"contains"}]},{"name":"Undertowers","arc":"Shire History","description":"The home of the Fairbairn family, an important Shire family. It houses the Red Book of Westmarch, a major historical source.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Great Smials","arc":"Shire History","description":"The major ancestral home of the Tooks, known for its extensive libraries containing historical records.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"part of"}]},{"name":"Bucklebury","aliases":["Buckland"],"arc":"Quest","description":"A region located east of the Brandywine River and connected to the Shire, known for its protective Hedge and resistance against foes.","recentEvents":"Mr. Baggins is planning to depart from Buckland under threat from Black Riders, with Fredegar Bolger staying behind.","relationships":[{"location":"Shire","relationship":"Bordered by and connected to"},{"location":"Old Forest","relationship":"Adjacent to, with the Old Forest seen as a dangerous but necessary route"}]},{"name":"Rivendell","aliases":["Imladris"],"arc":"Council of Elrond","description":"A hidden valley refuge for Elves and other noble beings.","recentEvents":"The Council of Elrond discusses the fate of the One Ring and decides on a mission for Frodo.","relationships":[{"location":"Mordor","relationship":"The goal destination for the ring's destruction"},{"location":"Shire","rel