nor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Gondor","description":"Grandson of the Steward Faramir, author of the abbreviated version of The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Wrote The Tale of Aragorn and Arwen for the history of Gondor."},{"name":"Findegil","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Many Years Ago","currentLocation":"Minas Tirith","description":"King's Writer who completed the Thain's Book.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Completed a copy of the Red Book in Minas Tirith."},{"name":"Lobelia Sackville-Baggins","importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3","currentLocation":"Bywater","description":"Hobbit from Sackville-Baggins family, rival of the Baggins family, known for her jealousy and desire to inherit Bag End.","relationships":[{"character":"Otho Sackville-Baggins","relationship":"Husband"},{"character":"Bilbo Baggins","relationship":"Rival"},{"character":"Frodo Baggins","relationship":"Antagonist"}],"recentEvents":"Visited Frodo and pestered him about Bilbo's will, accusing him of being a Brandybuck."},{"name":"Samwise Gamgee","aliases":["Sam","Samwise","Sam Gamgee","Sammy","Sam Gardner","Hamfast's son","Hamfast Gamgee's Son"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the Fellowship","currentLocation":"Tol Brandir","description":"Frodo's loyal and devoted companion, a brave and unyielding hobbit who shares the burden of the quest.","relationships":[{"character":"Frodo","relationship":"Travel companion and closest friend"},{"character":"Aragorn","relationship":"Travel companion"},{"character":"Boromir","relationship":"Travel companion"}],"recentEvents":"Expressed fear while passing through the chasm towards the Argonath."},{"name":"Gildor","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"None","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An Elf who encountered Frodo and his companions, giving them guidance and warning 